cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper is primarily focused on measuring the security of cyber networks under advanced persistent threats (APTs). This falls under the domain of cryptography and security. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with the analysis of cyber networks and their security. This falls under the domain of social and information networks. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the security of cyber networks, which is a crucial aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses theoretical analysis and computer simulation to understand the influence of different factors on the security of cyber networks. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper models the APT-based cyber attack-defense process as an individual-level dynamical system. This falls under the domain of data structures and algorithms.
